20 Minute Salmon Cakes
from Marian Burros' 20-Minute Menus
2 servings

15.5 oz canned salmon
1/2 serrano or other chili pepper, deseeded
4 oz red onion, cut into chunks
2 Tbsp bread crumbs
1/2 tsp cinnamon
1 tsp cumin
1/8 tsp cloves
1/2 tsp ground coriander
2 Tbsp corn, safflower, or canola oil

Rinse salmon and remove skin

Turn on food processor; add chunks of onion and chili half; process just
until coarsely minced

Add salmon, bread crumbs, cinnamon, cumin, cloves, and coriander and
process until paste is formed.  If necessary, add more crumbs to make
patty that will hold its shape.

Shape mixture into 4 patties.

Heat oil in skillet over medium heat.  Saute patties on both sides until
browned.

Serve patties on warm flour tortillas with salsa, garnished with salsa,
cilantro leaves, and yogurt.
